2026-03-29 | Make Strings Equal with Distance-2 Swaps

	Question
Can we rearrange s1 using these swaps to match s2?

	Approach
1.	Observe:
		You can freely rearrange characters within each group.
2.	So for both strings:
		sort characters in positions (0,2)  
		sort characters in positions (1,3)  
3.	If both groups match between s1 and s2 → return true  
4.	Else → return false  

	Time Complexity
	O(1)

	Space Complexity
	O(1)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    bool canBeEqual(string s1, string s2) {

        vector<char> a1 = {s1[0], s1[2]};
        vector<char> b1 = {s2[0], s2[2]};

        vector<char> a2 = {s1[1], s1[3]};
        vector<char> b2 = {s2[1], s2[3]};

        sort(a1.begin(), a1.end());
        sort(b1.begin(), b1.end());
        sort(a2.begin(), a2.end());
        sort(b2.begin(), b2.end());

        return (a1 == b1) && (a2 == b2);
    }
};

	Key Insight
Swaps with distance 2 restrict movement:
characters can only move within fixed index groups.  

So the problem reduces to:
		checking if both strings have the same multiset of characters in each group.
